A man died in Elysian Park when a hillside collapsed on the tent where he was sleeping.
Storms in Southern California have caused chaos, with floods, mudslides, and power outages.
Rescuers saved people trapped in cars and homes, while others tragically lost their lives.
The relentless rain has overwhelmed the region, leading to road closures and evacuations.
